H0.text: Who won the 1952 US Presidential election. Harry S. Truman

H1.text: Who won the 1952 US Presidential election. Adlai Stevenson

H2.text: Who won the 1952 US Presidential election. Robert A. Taft

H3.text: Who won the 1952 US Presidential election. Eisehower

A4.text: The Republican ticket of general Dwight D. Eisenhower and senator Richard Nixon defeated the Democratic ticket of Illinois Governor Adlai Stevenson II and senator John Sparkman in a landslide victory

A5.text: Eisenhower won a decisive victory by winning over 55% of the popular vote and carrying 39 of the 48 states
